        <h1>Registration for the 2021 STFC Summer School</h1>
        
        <p> Application to attend the summer school is open to anyone but is aimed in particular at PhD students starting their degrees in Autumn 2021. Please note that places will be limited, and as such an application does not guarantee you a place on the course. In the event the course is oversubscribed, places will be allocated on a first-come, first-served basis. </p>
        
        <h1> Finances </h1>
        
        <p> The <strong> cost to non-STFC funded PhD students is Â£500. </strong> This includes accommodation and food in one of Durham's colleges. Students starting PhDs <strong>funded by the STFC can attend the course free of charge.</strong> </p> 
        
        <p> In the unlikely event that we are unable to run the course in person, it will be held online using Zoom and there will be no charge to any attendees. </p>
        
        <h1> Apply </h1> 
        
        <p>To apply for a place on the course please fill out the <a href ="https://forms.office.com/r/H0amz2dqaR">application form</a>. Shortly afterwards, you should receive an email confirming the details you have submitted and we will be in touch with further information in due course. </p>
        
        
